abstract: Cornell’s Danny Nathan provides a running diary of what it’s like for a player in the week leading up to the N.C.A. tournament.
snippet: Cornell’s Danny Nathan provides a running diary of what it’s like for a player in the week leading up to the N.C.A. tournament.
lead_paragraph: When it comes to getting a player’s perspective, The Quad knows where to turn. That’s right, we went back to the well at Cornell. And why not? Jon Jaques gave us some fascinating insight when the Big Red’s men’s basketball team made an appearance in the N.C.A.A. tournament. Now Danny Nathan, a senior midfielder on the lacrosse team, will share some of his experiences as he and his teammates get ready for N.C.A.A. tournament play. In this first installment, Danny gives us a running diary, beginning with the tournament selection show and encompassing topics as varied as a team dinner at Chili’s and the sexual shenanigans of the ancient Greeks. Make sure to check back at The Quad to read more from Danny as the tournament progresses.

abstract: College football’s top officials decided that the method for determining a national champion will stay the same until at least January of 2015.
snippet: College football’s top officials decided that the method for determining a national champion will stay the same until at least January of 2015.
lead_paragraph: HOLLYWOOD, Fla.  After years of research and discussion, major college football’s top executives gathered here to finally have a formal discussion about changing the sport’s controversial and polarizing postseason format.
headline_main: No Change Imminent for B.C.S. Format
headline_print_headline: Most B.C.S. Chiefs Say They Like It the Way It Is
